CS:GO Tournaments

Counter-Strike: Global Offensive is among the most popular and well-known multiplayer shooters in the world. Millions of people turn on their computer to play CS:GO every day, to break into the world of battles, adrenaline and experience the sense of victory over the enemy. This is not just a game. Counter-Strike: Global Offensive tournaments are part of the esports world, which has long occupied his niche among other types of entertainment.

Once there were non-professional tournaments for beginners and amateurs, but today esports is a brand new and fully completed show. Now we have big tournaments including international ones and the competitions that the whole world is watching. It is not surprising that many people want to get into this sport and become a part of history, participate in tournaments that aggregate huge stadiums. Not everyone knows where to start, but there is always a solution.

How to become a pro player? Easy-peasy! You just need to sharpen your skills. To do so, you may start with something little: enter CS:GO tournaments for beginners, for example. You don't need to have a full team of five players at the start, as your individual skill is what matters at the beginning of your esports path.

In addition to the usual practice in matchmaking, sometimes you have to try yourself in competitive matches. These are completely different emotions, and also the ability to get rewards changes the approach to the game.

The most popular are online tournaments, and we have a special platform to hold them. wegamingtour! Esports team have created a series of weekly CS:GO tournaments for all those who wish to join the world of Counter-Strike, including beginners. Here you can compete with other players in any convenient format, as well as make new acquaintances, discuss the problems of CS:GO and even find a team.

Free tournaments for beginners is a great way to acquire skills at playing Counter-Strike, as well as prepare for competitions with stronger opponents.

Who can participate in CS:GO Tournaments?

Anyone can participate, just register on our website and link your Steam account with the game to the created profile. Also, you must have prime status in CS:GO - i.e. you had to purchase CS:GO, or reach level 21 of the in-game profile.

What are the prizes for winning the CS: GO tournament?

Participants who took prize places receive Steam certificates, more detailed information is listed on the page of each individual tournament.

What are the tournament formats? Can I participate alone, or with a friend / team?

Yes, we have tournaments in the following formats: 1v1, 2v2 and 5v5, so everyone can find and try themselves in the most suitable.

How often are tournaments held?

Tournaments are held on a daily basis with a different start period, so any participant will find the most convenient time for themselves.
